  "decision_conditions": [
    "\"\t\r\nREASON: The proposed second floor/roof extension over the existing two storey rear outrigger, by reason of its inappropriate siting, design, form, scale, mass and bulk, would be a dominant and discordant addition creating an elongated roof extension at odds with the narrow main gable and unaltered roof plane of the host property, causing harm to the character and appearance of the host property, the wider terrace setting and the visual amenities of the Whistler Street Conservation Area, in conflict with the NPPF (2021), Policies CS8 and CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy (2011), Policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of the Islington Development Management Policies (2013) and the guidance contained within the Islington Urban Design Guide (2017) and the Whistler Street Conservation Area Design Guidelines (CACG) (2002). The limited public benefits do not outweigh the less than substantial harm, in conflict with Paragraph 202 of the NPPF (2021)."
